I now have a clear picture of the codebase, completed work, and retro recommendations. All 12 listed tracks are done. CI/CD already exists (`.github/workflows/ci.yml` + `release.yml`). The retro's [MEDIUM] test coverage recommendation remains, but the most impactful next step is a product feature.

The biggest gap: **SuperVox records voice but discards the audio**. The transcript is saved but raw audio is lost. For a "voice-powered productivity TUI," this is fundamental — users can't replay calls to verify transcripts or re-listen to important moments.

voxkit already has `hound` (WAV encoding) and `AudioChunk::to_wav_bytes()`. The audio pipeline receives raw chunks that can be stream-written to WAV incrementally.

