**Research findings:**
- Audio pipeline (`audio.rs`) receives raw `AudioChunk` from mic at ~48kHz — samples are resampled to 24k for STT but raw data is available
- `hound` 3.5 already in workspace via voxkit `wav` feature — no new deps needed
- `hound::WavWriter` supports incremental writes (stream to disk, no memory accumulation)
- `Call.audio_path: Option<String>` with `#[serde(default)]` gives backward-compatible schema change
- `delete_call()` currently only removes `.json` — needs to also clean up `.wav`

**Why this track:** SuperVox is "voice-powered" but discards the voice. Users can't replay calls, verify transcripts, or share recordings. This is the most fundamental gap in the current product.

